{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":37413,"duration_api_ms":37379,"num_turns":8,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"f59d5737-1157-4868-a5b5-b7f607c434c1","total_cost_usd":0.232399,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":23166,"cache_read_input_tokens":109173,"output_tokens":1320,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":23166,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":5,"outputTokens":1320,"cacheReadInputTokens":109173,"cacheCreationInputTokens":23166,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.232399,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Both amendments identify genuine data integrity issues in the plan_hash backfill logic. Amendment fr-2-e54db26f correctly identifies that snapshot_plan_hash() reads the current snapshot, which persist_plan() can advance independently (service.rs:370), causing legacy rows to be mislabeled with a newer plan version. Amendment fr-2-371a0969 correctly identifies an asymmetry: backfill_terminal_entry() (lines 2670-2689) only copies a caller-supplied hash with no snapshot fallback, while the non-terminal path (lines 3246-3249) does attempt snapshot backfill. Both are real correctness gaps that warrant tests and fixes.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-2-e54db26f","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified in source: lines 2916-2918 and 3246-3249 call snapshot_plan_hash() which reads the current snapshot plan_hash. persist_plan() at service.rs:370 sets snapshot.plan_hash to the hash of the latest plan JSON, advancing it on every plan update. A legacy row created under plan v1 that has plan_hash=None will be stamped with the current snapshot hash at replay time, which could be v2 or later. This is a silent data integrity bug — it misattributes work to the wrong plan version. The fix is sound: avoid snapshot-based backfill when the original plan version cannot be determined, and add a regression test covering legacy rows that span a plan evolution."},{"amendment_id":"fr-2-371a0969","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified in source: backfill_terminal_entry() (lines 2685-2689) only sets plan_hash when the caller provides Some(plan_hash). The terminal-replay path at lines 3218-3224 passes plan_hash directly from the caller. If a legacy finalized row has plan_hash=None and the caller also provides None (the common legacy case), the function will backfill run_id, outcome_detail, and finished_at but leave plan_hash as None. This is inconsistent with the non-terminal completion path at lines 3246-3249 which does attempt snapshot-based backfill. The requested regression test — preseeding a terminal row with plan_hash=None and replaying with caller plan_hash=None — is the correct way to document and guard against this asymmetry."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"09f403cb-99ec-4916-9495-640a4abe4af3"}
